                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1369">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1639</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                    <gloss type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-29T13:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1915, 1 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 30, 10.15 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>540. Your telegram No. 460, March 3 [4].<note n="1" xml:id="d1369fn1">See
                        footnote 2, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_962">p.
                        962</ref>.</note> Question of indemnity for families of victims of British
                    bombardment still in suspense. Authorities demanded £4,000, I offered £40.
                        <persName corresp="#p_EP1">Enver</persName> then suggested £100 for each
                    victim’s family. Meanwhile English prisoners appear to have been allowed to
                    return to Aleppo and reside there in comparative freedom.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
